Description: Fragment of neck and round handle rising to sharp turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with winged caduceus symbol.
Curator's comments: Ink '1302' (an IG XIII 1 number erroneously allocated); paper label 'Type of the Rhodian manubria'. Name Eukleitos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0296.25.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (144)
